HEADWORD: Sumpter
<hw>Sump"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>sommetier</ets> the driver of a pack horse; akin to OF. & F.
<ets>sommier</ets> a pack horse, L. <ets>sagmarius</ets>, fr.
<ets>sagma</ets> a pack saddle, in LL., a load, Gr. <?/ a pack saddle,
fr. <?/ to pack, load; cf. Skr. <ets>saj</ets>, <ets>sa⟦ntil⟧j</ets>, to
hang on. Cf. <er>Seam</er> a weight, <er>Summer</er> a beam.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The driver of a pack horse.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Skeat.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pack; a burden.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An animal, especially a horse, that carries packs or
burdens; a baggage horse.</def> <rj><au>Holinshed.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sumpter</ent>⟦br⟧

